# Cloudflare Pages headers config.
# Mirrors what kits/fitness-kit/server/static.ts (Hono on Railway) sets per
# response, so showcase deployed to CF Pages behaves the same as a fitness-kit
# Bun-server deploy.
#
# Syntax: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/
# Files in apps/ui-native-showcase/public/* are copied verbatim into dist/
# during `expo export --platform web`, so this lands at dist/_headers.

# Hashed asset chunks (entry-XXXX.js, *.png with hash) live under these
# prefixes. Filenames include a content hash so a new version always gets
# a new path → cache forever.
/_expo/static/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *

# Everything else — HTML, manifest, fonts, the index entrypoint.
# DO NOT set Cache-Control here. Cloudflare Pages MERGES headers from
# every matching rule (it doesn't do most-specific-wins), so a Cache-Control
# directive on `/*` would be appended to the immutable directive set above
# for /_expo/static/* and /assets/* — and browsers obey the most-restrictive
# concatenated value, which would defeat the immutable asset caching.
#
# CF Pages' default for HTML is `cache-control: public, max-age=0,
# must-revalidate` which is functionally equivalent to no-store for the
# purposes of "user always gets the latest bundle reference" — the HTML
# is ~5 KB so the round-trip is cheap and bundle hashes update immediately.
/*
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
  Access-Control-Allow-Methods: GET, OPTIONS
  Access-Control-Allow-Headers: Content-Type
  Access-Control-Max-Age: 86400
  # Allow iframe embed from any origin — the showcase is designed to be
  # embedded by apps/ui-native-storybook-preview/ for marketing surfaces.
  # X-Frame-Options is omitted on purpose; CSP frame-ancestors is the
  # modern equivalent and supports wildcard origins.
  Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors *
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
